SIMPLE: magnesia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnesia
<hw>Mag*ne"si*a</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Magnesia</ets>, fem. of <ets>Magnesius</ets> of the country
Magnesia, Gr. <grk>h` Magnhsi`a li`qos</grk> a magnet. Cf.
<er>Magnet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A light earthy white
substance, consisting of magnesium oxide (<chform>MgO</chform>), and
obtained by heating magnesium hydrate or carbonate, or by burning
magnesium. It has a slightly alkaline reaction, and is used in medicine
as a mild antacid laxative. See <er>Magnesium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Magnesia alba</b></col> <ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Med.
Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a bulky white amorphous substance, consisting of a
hydrous basic carbonate of magnesium, and used as a mild
cathartic.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnesian</ent>⟦br⟧
